canonical:
  title: 祖師禮懺祝上疏
  author: 釋無畏
  language: lzh
  text: 人傳一人甘露灑霑於中國世止九世餘波流及於東韓遺風猶有存焉懺席宜無廢也伏念幸逢盛際叨受懿封內虧觀照之功外現威儀之相誠爲斷佛種者濫作傳法燈人玆値良辰略陳熏範一禮一懺業障報障煩惱障之滅除三止三觀性空相空畢竟空之淸淨如斯施作無㝵照詳伏願優承諸祖之加亦被多天之護動罔不吉災禍殄於未然永孚于休壽祺至於無極
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 祖師禮懺祝上疏
  author: 釋無畏
  language: lzh
  text: 人傳一人。甘露灑霑於中國。世止九世。餘波流及於東韓。遺風猶有存焉。懺席宜無廢也。伏念幸逢盛際。叨受懿封。內虧觀照之功。外現威儀之相。誠爲斷佛種者。濫作傳法燈人。玆値良辰。略陳熏範。一禮一懺。業障報障煩惱障之滅除。三止三觀。性空相空畢竟空之淸淨。如斯施作。無㝵照詳。伏願優承諸祖之加。亦被多天之護。動罔不吉。災禍殄於未然。永孚于休。壽祺至於無極。
korean:
  title: 조사 예참을 축원하는 글
  author: 석무외
  language: kor
  text: 한 사람씩 전해 온 감로(甘露)가 중국에 고루 적시고, 아홉 대로 흘러 내린 종파가 멀리 동방에 미쳤으니, 그 끼친 바가 아직 남아 있사온데, 예참의 자리를 어찌 없앨 수 있으리까. 생각하건대 다행히 융성한 시대를 만나 감히 훌륭한 벼슬을 받았으나, 안으로는 관조(觀照)의 공이 모자라고 밖으로는 위의의 모양만 나타내니, 실로 불종(佛種)을 끊게 된 자로서 외람되게 법등(法燈)을 전할 지위에 놓여 있사오매, 이제 좋은 때를 가려 약간의 훈범(熏範)을 베푸나이다. 한 번 예배와 한 번 참회에 업장(業障)ㆍ보장(報障)ㆍ번뇌장(煩惱障)이 소멸되고, 세 번 정지와 세 번 관찰에 성공(性空)ㆍ상공(相空)ㆍ필경공(畢竟空)이 청정하오니, 이러한 베품을 걸림 없이 비춰주시기 바라옵니다. 원하건대, 모든 조사의 가호를 넉넉히 받고 많은 천왕의 도움을 입어서, 하는 일이 다 상서로워 재화가 미연에 없어지고, 길이 아름다운 복을 누려 수명이 끝 없음에 이르게 하옵소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0190&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Prayer for Reverence and Repentance to the Ancestral Masters
  author: Seok Mu-oe
  language: eng
  text: |-
    From master to disciple, the nectar of dharma has been transmitted, drenching the lands of China with its grace. Through nine generations the lineage has flowed, reaching far to these eastern shores, and still its blessed influence endures. How then could we ever abandon the seat of reverence and repentance?

    I reflect that fortune has granted me this flourishing age, and undeservedly I have received this honored office. Yet inwardly my practice of clear contemplation remains incomplete, and outwardly I merely wear the appearance of dignified conduct. Truly, I am one who has severed the Buddha's seed, yet presumptously I stand as a keeper of the dharma lamp. On this auspicious day, I humbly offer these practices. Through each bow and each act of repentance, the three obstacles—karma, retribution, and affliction—dissolve into emptiness. Through each threefold restraint and threefold insight, the three kinds of emptiness—of self, of phenomena, and of ultimate reality—become pure and luminous.

    May these humble offerings bear fruit without obstruction. I pray to receive abundantly the blessings of all the ancestral masters, and the protection of the celestial guardians. Let all my endeavors be auspicious, and calamities be prevented before they arise. May I enjoy enduring good fortune, and may my years extend without limit.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'nectar of dharma' (甘露) refers to Buddhist teachings, often metaphorically described as sweet dew that nourishes spiritual growth.
  - key: ''
    value: 'The ''three obstacles'' (三障) are foundational concepts in Buddhist thought: karma obstacle (actions and their consequences), retribution obstacle (suffering from past actions), and affliction obstacle (mental defilements).'
  - key: ''
    value: The 'three kinds of emptiness' refer to advanced Buddhist philosophical doctrines regarding the absence of inherent self-nature in persons, phenomena, and ultimately all existence.
